<title type="html"><![CDATA[Definition: Ta'teel]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1106&amp;p=1170#p1170"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">Definition: Ta'teel - Shaykh Muhammad ibn Saalih al Uthaymeen</span></strong><br /><em>Source: Sharh ul ‘aqeedatil waasitiyyah of Shaykh Muhammad ibn Saalih al ‘Uthaymeen rahimahullaah page 72</em><br /><br />Translator Nasser ibn Najam – words in brackets and footnotes are the translator’s<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Meaning:</span></strong><br />Rejecting the Names and Attributes which Allaah has affirmed for Himself<br /><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Explanation:</span></strong><br />Ta’teel has the meaning “emptying” and “abandoning”, just as in His statement, He the Most High:<br /><ul>…a well which is mu’attalah…</ul><em>Soorah al Hajj (22) aayah 45</em><br /><br />Meaning: empty and abandoned.<br /><br />And what is meant by <em>ta’teel</em>[1] is:<br /><br />Rejecting the Names and Attributes which Allaah has affirmed for Himself, whether that be all (of them) or a portion (of them), and whether that is done by tahreef (distortion) or through outright rejection – all of this is called ta’teel.<br /><br />So the <em>ahl us sunnah wal jamaa’ah</em> do not make ta’teel of any of the Names of Allaah nor of any of the Attributes of Allaah nor do they deny them; rather they affirm them with a complete affirmation.<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Footnotes:</span></strong><br />[1] In this particular instance, i.e. by Ibn Taymiyyaah rahimahullaah in Al Waasitiyyah<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Sun Feb 12, 2017 12:18 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
